.TH "NAVIGATIONCURRENTENTRYCHANGEEVENT.NAVIGATIONCURRENTENTRYCHANGEEVENT" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent.NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent \-
NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent: NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent()
constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent()\f[B]\f[R] constructor
creates a new \f[CR]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[R] object.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent(type, init)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A string representing the type of event.
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R]
An object that, \f[I]in addition to the properties defined in
\f[CI]Event()\f[I]\f[R], has the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]from\f[R]
A \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] object representing the location
being navigated to.
.TP
\f[B]navigationType\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The type of the navigation that resulted in the change.
Possible values are \f[CR]push\f[R], \f[CR]reload\f[R],
\f[CR]replace\f[R], and \f[CR]traverse\f[R].
Defaults to \f[CR]null\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
A developer would not use this constructor manually.
A new \f[CR]NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent\f[R] object is constructed
when a handler is invoked as a result of the
\f[CR]currententrychange\f[R] event firing.
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqcurrententrychange\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event.navigationType);
});
.EE
